prop_common.description: Enjoy spectacular city light and San Jacinto/San Gabriel/Santa Ana Mountain views from this amazing DR Horton built home! Perfectly positioned to soak in one of Corona's best views, this home is located in the coveted neighborhood of Hidden Crest which is right off of the new Foothill Parkway extension, making your commute a breeze! This home features a gracious open floor plan, which is evident from the moment you step in the front door and cast your eyes upon the beautiful engineered wood flooring which leads all the way back to the open family room and kitchen, providing a glimpse of the enticing view. Boasting over 3300 square feet with three bedrooms, a den off the entry AND a 400 square foot loft located upstairs which also has a large storage room/closet including an access door to the attic- the options are endless- this could potentially be a five bedroom home if one was so inclined. The three bathrooms include a half bath off of the main living area, a full bath next to the ancillary bedrooms which features a dual sink vanity, and a master bathroom that is huge with a tub and separate shower, with two vanities of it's own. The spacious master bedroom features not one, but two walk-in closets, along with a great view! The upgraded kitchen features beautiful granite counters with a large rounded-edge island, and stainless appliances including a double-oven, and is open to the oversized family room making it the perfect place to entertain all of your guests!

prop_common.description: Welcome home to 826 Live Oak Place in Corona, a lovely 2 bedroom open floor plan Townhome. This turnkey home features a good sized kitchen with gas range, built-in microwave, dishwasher, counter top bar and with a window over looking the grounds. Eating area with sliding glass doors leading out to the patio/sitting area. Cozy fireplace in the living room with vaulted ceilings. With two master bedrooms upstairs complete with their own bathrooms you'll have plenty of room in this home. This Townhome has a 2 car garage with storage and direct access to the home. Close to the 91 freeway, Orange County and the toll roads. This is a planned unit development and the homeowners association offers a beautiful gated pool and spa area, playground and peaceful grounds with a waterfall. Accessible from Green River. Highly desired floor plan and location. Don't miss your dream home.

This four unit apartment has an attractive unit mix of 2 one bedroom / one bathroom units, 1 two bedroom / one bathroom unit and 1 three bedroom / one bathroom unit. The apartment is located within a short driving distance of two of the areas biggest employers, The Corona Regional Medical Center & Watson Pharmaceuticals. These employers alone have more than 2,200 employees. The properties close proximity makes it a great fit for medical staff and blue collar workers alike. The property is also ideally suited for families, being within a short distance from Corona High School and its more than 3,100 Students. The situation of the community also provides direct access to the 91 and 15 freeways, for convenient commuting. 419 E 8th St, Corona, CA 92879 is found within the neighborhood referred to as City Center neighborhood of Corona. Corona City Center is an urban neighborhood, with real estate vacancies in Corona City Center below five percent, which is lower than one will find in nearly 70% of American neighborhoods.
